<h2>Welcome!</h2>

<p>DC Metro Metrics is a project dedicated to collecting and sharing publicly available data related to the DC Metrorail system.<p>

This website compiles data which is not availability anywhere else, including:
<ul>
<li>A <a href="/escalators/directory">directory</a> of all 588 escalators in the DC Metrorail system</li>
<li>Performance history for each escalator in the system.</li>
<li>Escalator reliability <a href="/escalators/rankings">rankings</a></li>
<li>Escalator availability by <a href="/stations">station</a></li>
<li>Crowdsourced Twitter <a href="/hotcars">reports</a> of #wmata #hotcar's.</li>
</ul>

<p>This website and its features are a work in progress.
If you have any questions or comments, or would like to get involved,
please contact me at <a href="mailto:info@dcmetrometrics.com" target="_blank">info@dcmetrometrics.com.</a></p>

<p>Thanks for visiting!</p>

